HEADWORD: Xylotomous
<hw>Xy*lot"o*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>xylo-</ets> + root of Gr. <grk>te`mnein</grk> to cut.]</ety>
